<p>How I can extract a subterm from a term in Prolog?</p>  <p>An example, I am trying to extract a predicate called <strong>r</strong> wherever it is but I do know how. Any help? </p>  <p>term_extraxtions(<strong>s(n(1),t(3,4,r(2,4)))</strong>,ModifiedTerm,ExtractedTerm)  will be as follows. </p>  <p>ModifiedTerm = <strong>s(n(1),t(3,4))</strong>.</p>  <p>ExtractedTerm = <strong>r(2,4)</strong>.</p>